section.def:
body (遺體) means the dead
            body or part thereof of any human being or any still born child, but does not include
            ashes resulting from the cremation thereof;

paragraph.content:
the Tung Wah Hospital Repository situated at Sandy Bay, Hong Kong;
                        or (78
                            of 1999 s. 7)

the date and number of the death certificate and of any permit for the
                    burial, cremation, importation into or removal from Hong Kong, as the case may
                    be, of such remains;
